# Phase 4 / Plan 04-07 / REPORT-06 — Cloudflare Pages routing.
#
# /share/* is forwarded first-hit through the Supabase Edge Function
# `og-share-card`. The function does User-Agent-based routing:
#   - Bot UA  -> 200 + minimal OG-meta HTML + x-robots-tag: noindex,nofollow.
#   - Human UA -> 302 redirect to /share/<token>?fallback=1, which lands on
#                 the SPA index.html and TanStack Router takes over.
#
# IMPORTANT — replace <project-ref> before the production deploy. The value
# is your Supabase project reference id (Dashboard -> Project Settings ->
# General -> Reference ID). Plan 04-07 Task 8 (human checkpoint) walks the
# designer through swapping the literal token.
#
# Until the project-ref is filled in, this rule is a NO-OP (Cloudflare
# Pages rejects rules with a literal '<' in the destination URL). The SPA
# fallback below still ships, so the designer's testing flow continues to
# work locally without the OG card.

/share/*  https://<project-ref>.functions.supabase.co/og-share-card/:splat  200

# SPA fallback for every other path — TanStack Router resolves client-side.
/*  /index.html  200
